               <p>EIGHTH DAY. - FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 21.</p>
               <p>Third London Jury - before Mr. Common Sergeant.</p>
               <p>1955. 
               <persName id="t18270913-368-defend2636" type="defendantName">
                  EDWARD 
                  EVANS
               <interp inst="t18270913-368-defend2636" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-defend2636" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-defend2636" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-defend2636" type="age" value="18"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18270913-368-off2044" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-off2044" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-off2044" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18270913-368-cd2045" type="crimeDate">2d of September</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-368-off2044 t18270913-368-cd2045"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 4s., the goods of a certain person, whose name is unknown, from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-368-person2637">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COLTON
               <interp inst="t18270913-368-person2637" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-person2637" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-person2637" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On Sunday evening, the 2d of September, I was going down Long-lane, with Cadby, at half-past nine o'clock - I saw the prisoner, with two others, behind a gentleman and lady - I saw one of them take the handkerchief, and give it to the prisoner - I seized two of them, and called the gentleman, who stood by, when we got the handkerchief from the prisoner; but we struggled across the road, and the gentleman got away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-368-person2638">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CADBY
               <interp inst="t18270913-368-person2638" type="surname" value="CADBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-person2638" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-person2638" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Colton. I saw the prisoner and two others; one of them took the handkerchief, and gave it to the prisoner, who was behind him; this was just at the end of Long-lane.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270913-368-verdict2046" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-368-verdict2046" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
